which was then 13.<br>
<br>
I found the first reptile to challenge near the docks midway along the coast, and swinging my Langseax and a PGT I had picked up, soon chopped it into chunks of meat suitable for dinner. From there I went on to the next and the next, but while on the third or so a nasty dry bones skeleton decided to join in the battle against me and my health was dropping very fast when suddenly there were others of various races and creeds weighing in to help. I confess to being somewhat amazed at their kindness and charity in lending a hand to a mere dark elf female, for they could not know I was not in fact a follower of Innoruk as are so many of my kind, or thoroughly evil. Having seen the beasts both lying dead, the others bowed and left me alone again to pursue my solo battles, thoroughly healed and with a buff or two as well to protect me beyond the power of my arm and armour.<br>
<br>
The solo battles went on for a while, with similar assistance when there was need. Mostly I stayed apart from the others in the area, too proud to accept heals and buffs too often, and bound my own wounds or sat in silence on the dock while I mended. Then a young wood elf warrior named Kendryk arrived, and seeing that we belonged in fact to the same guild, we struck up a conversation and decided to try our luck together.<br>
<br>
I must say that for a member of such a weak race and a follower of a feminine goddess named Tunare, this Kendryk acquitted himself quite well in my company, bringing no shame at all to the warrior class. His bow shot true and often; the blows of his weapons landed squarely... Together we bested many a foe although our stock of bandages dwindled to nothing along the way. But there were many times when our adversaries proved too much for us - Kendryk died and was resurrected by his Tunare I think seven times, while I saw my own life blood pour out into the sand at least four times and yet came back (no god of course caused this, but purely warrior's fate). I will have to admit the wood elf died well each time and came back laughing. This is as it should be...<br>
<br>
In all, Kendryk was quite attentive as a companion and paid me many flattering compliments... Perhaps it is just as well Ayzreall was not in the vicinity? But after all, I am a dark elf and no matter any mild diversions with such weaker beings as wood elves, Ayzreall remains my destined mate and I will have no other while he remains at my side.<br>
<br>
Reaching my 15th season, I returned to Freeport to sneak some training from the warrior guild there (requiring a kind druid to give me wolf form to obtain) and set off for Highpass Hold, where I hope to meet up with my Ayzreall soon and challenge the denizens of Mucktail Gnolls.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
