<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fbe5b4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub44.ezboard.com/beverquestersofnorrath.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=suruli>Suruli</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 5<br> <font color=#8B4513>(7/4/01 4:15:00 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Oasis</span><hr size=1> Dark Elves stubborn? I know nothing of dwarves to compare to, but cannot imagine how you could possibly equate anything of me with those little stumpy fellows! Destiny is destiny. One must follow the path created for one... or at least know the true destination.<br>
<br>
Ordained, with due respect (as one must accord one's elders and the relatives of one's guildmates) I am certain you do Kendryk an injustice. Towns may run him out; fathers and husbands may lock him out; he presents such a fresh and delightful approach to certain things that I am certain women and daughters find ways to spend time in his company regardless.<br>
<br>
Hmmm ... yes, one must follow one's personal path and mine leads to Ayzreall in the end. This is only fitting. But ... one's path may have many shady bowers along the way, tempting one to dally and perhaps divert oneself ... er ... sip from a chance found well or stream ... ahem ... uh .... dip into ... Never mind.<br>
<br>
Following my sojourn in Oasis, I found my way to Highpass Hold and met Ayzreall there, who had been fighting gnolls in an attempt to prove his actual loyalty to the forces of good and gain faction there. In spite of having spent several seasons already slaying these beasts, the guards and citizens of Highpass still regard him most threateningly, presumably because he was forced to declare himself a follower of Innoruk. Although I know the truth of this matter, as do those of you in Victus Fortis, these inhabitants of Highpass Hold seem reluctant to allow him any benefit of doubt. I find that I myself may wander freely into the various inns and taverns there, and into Highkeep itself without danger, but then I worship fighting and the sword and no mere god.<br>
<br>
The group of halflings who invited us to join them on the gnoll ledge one day proved less than adequate companions in battle, and I have met no others worthy of the respect of such a warrior as myself. Ayzreall and I have been better off lying in wait in the passage from East Karana where we can pick off those gnolls who are foolish enough to wander our way. At times my mate raises up a giant skeleton pet to amuse and assist us, his powers of magic growing every day. I admire his skill, and more than once he has drained his own life rather than that of our opponents to save my life or heal me when the odds were great. I know that he relies upon my strong arm in these battles as I rely upon his magic. We are well matched as companions and as fighting duo ...<br>
<br>
Highpass is incredibly lonely when Ayzreall is not there. In his absence I purchased a fishing pole and bait and ventured to the pool beneath the falls there the other day, spending several hours in this quiet occupation with some success. I would rather be fighting .... I hear that Kendryk has arrived here from Oasis to test his blades upon gnoll hides, and remember his prowess in Oasis .... Perhaps, just perhaps, I may allow myself to test my memory of his um ... &quot;skill&quot; ... and uh ...<br>
<br>
I seem unaccountably to have lost track of what I was saying.<br>
<br>
~Suruli <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub44.ezboard.com/feverquestersofnorrathfrm17.showMessage?topicID=74.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub44.ezboard.com/feverquestersofnorrathfrm17.showMessage?topicID=81.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br></td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub44.ezboard.com/feverquestersofnorrathfrm17.emailToFriend?topicID=73.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub44.ezboard.com/feverquestersofnorrathfrm17.threadControl?topicID=73.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/classic/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub44.ezboard.com/feverquestersofnorrathfrm17.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=73.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub44.ezboard.com/feverquestersofnorrathfrm17.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=73.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub44.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName><option value="everquestersofnorrathfrm20">General Forum<option value="everquestersofnorrathfrm16">Gatherings of the Brave<option value="everquestersofnorrathfrm25">Bazaar of the Brave<option value="everquestersofnorrathfrm17">Tales and Roleplay<option value="everquestersofnorrathfrm15">Questing<option value="everquestersofnorrathfrm18">Honour Role <option value="everquestersofnorrathfrm19">Dishonourable Denizens<option value="everquestersofnorrat